I am a constant note-taker, but also, note keeper. This app is my go-to for all important, long term notes. (I previously had issues with self inflicted, accidental delections, but, the update of an "Undo" button, fixed this issue. Thank you!!) This app has since supplanted all other note apps. I prefer it over OneNote, for organizational purposes, and the ability to read back, the text to speech feature, is invaluable for preventing overlooked mistakes. Huge Fan!!!

This app is definitely the most innovative and useful by far, and I would definitely recommend it to others looking for a functional notepad app. The notepad has some great features like resizing/zoom, attaching documents, and customising both the notepad document itself as well as the exterior of the book as you see it on the nifty little shelves. A few qualms though; The menu buttons inside the notepad are confusing and in the way, upon exiting to the home screen (I'm on a Nexus 10) and returning to the document, the colour and text preferences return to default, it would have been nice to see an option to actually draw/insert pictures into the actual document, rather than just as an attachment with an irritatingly small preview pane. Great app, but it doesn't come with all of the practical things one would ask for in a 'pro notepad'.  Update: App seems to be loading much faster now, and the bug with the document preferences has been fixed. Bumped up to four stars. =) Happy Apping!
